main event: Two USAF navigators reported observing an unidentified aerial object emitting a flickering bluish-white light at Mt. Palomar, California, on September 26, 1950.
interesting points: The object moved at a high speed covering approximately 200 horizontal degrees in 2-3 minutes,The sighting occurred under clear weather conditions,The observers perceived the light as a flickering star,Sound emitted by the object was described as swishing and similar to rocket exhaust,No exhaust trail was observed during the sighting.
witness description: USAF navigators, Captain and another lieutenant (names redacted)
